(164, 13706, 'a:7:{s:12:\"cfdb7_status\";s:6:\"unread\";s:8:\"fullname\";s:12:\"Val Subbaiah\";s:5:\"email\";s:16:\"val@animaker.com\";s:5:\"phone\";s:14:\"+91 9740889714\";s:7:\"company\";s:14:\"Animaker, Inc.\";s:8:\"comments\";s:1186:\"Hello Team 8K Miles,\r\n\r\nAnimaker website (https:&#047;&#047;www.animaker.com) is hosted on Amazon AWS.\r\nThe website &quot;crashed&quot; yesterday February 16 2018 at 8:40 AM. \r\nWhat we found out was AWS RDS goes into sleep mode.\r\nWe reached out to Amazon Support. We also reached out to another partner.\r\nAfter about 8 hours yesterday, the site was &quot;up&quot;. \r\n\r\nTroubleshooting done:\r\nTroubleshooting Steps:\r\nWe have disabled the bot and crawlers on webserver\r\nChecked the IPs and connections from HTTPD access log\r\nBlocked two IPs\r\nChecked  Wait_timeout and interactive_timeout setting which has value 180.\r\n\r\nThere still seems to be issues with RDS. We are still figuring out why RDS goes into sleep mode.\r\n\r\nThe partner who we had reached out has never handled RDS issues. \r\nIf you have handled RDS issues and can figure &quot;why&quot; RDS goes into sleep mode, please let us know.\r\n\r\nWe have a team in Chennai that was working with the AWS partner. If you think you have knowledge and expertise in\r\nRDS, I will connect you to them.\r\n \r\nThank you for your valuable time and with warm regards,\r\n\r\nVal Subbaiah | Animaker, Inc. | +91 9740889741 (Bangalore) | val@animaker.com\r\n\";s:10:\"department\";s:17:\"sales@8kmiles.com\";}', '2018-02-16 22:54:58'),
