(277, 13706, 'a:7:{s:12:\"cfdb7_status\";s:4:\"read\";s:8:\"fullname\";s:11:\"James Baker\";s:5:\"email\";s:20:\"jbaker30@calpoly.edu\";s:5:\"phone\";s:10:\"7033034233\";s:7:\"company\";s:8:\"Cal Poly\";s:8:\"comments\";s:3278:\"Cal Poly &#047; Medical Security Event &#047; California Cyber Innovation Challenge &#047; Donation Request\r\n\r\nThe Governor’s Office of Business Development has asked Cal Poly to host this year’s California Cyber Innovation Challenge.  This year’s competition will focus on medical cyber security. I wanted to see if you could point me in the right direction to speak with your team regarding a donation. Below are the details for the event.  Please feel free to contact me directly with any questions at 703.303.4233.\r\n\r\nRespectfully,\r\nJames Baker\r\n\r\n\r\nCALIFORNIA CYBER INNOVATION CHALLENGE\r\nThe California Cybersecurity Institute (CCI) of San Luis Obispo, California is excited to announce the launch of the 2018 California Cyber Innovation Challenge (CCIC). The CCIC is a statewide high school cybersecurity competition designed to introduce more students to cybersecurity as a future course of study or career. Cybersecurity challenges provide unique opportunities for businesses to proactively address their cybersecurity skills gaps, while simultaneously expanding access to technology career pathways for all Californians.\r\n \r\nThe CCIC will begin with regional qualifying rounds in spring 2018. Twenty teams will be drawn from these regional competitions and an “At-Large” selection process to participate in the state championship round on June 23-25 at the CCI. This year’s competition will highlight challenges associated with securing healthcare information and devices. This critical area is steadily growing in importance as we continue to push the boundaries in medical technology versus the looming cyber threats that face the medical community.\r\n \r\nWho can participate?\r\nThe CCIC is open to all California high schools.  Last year’s event featured an immersive, forensics training scenario with 16 cars, 64 high school students, and team of professionals from government, industry, and education.  Learn more about this year’s event at: https:&#047;&#047;youtu.be&#047;PrLTmRE7WGM \r\n\r\nCybersecurity and Medical\r\nThis year’s challenge will be themed around cybersecurity and medical.  The competition will take place in a medical office scenario at the California Cybersecurity Institute.  The competition will focus on both the ethical and technical issues of a Ransomware attack on a medical facility.  \r\n \r\nWe need sponsors — Can you help?\r\nThe CCIC is a California-focused, state-wide cybersecurity competition with no registration fees. We rely on contributions from companies and individuals interested in developing the next generation of cyber defenders. Sponsors are encouraged to attend the event and support the teams\r\n \r\nBe a Cyber-Difference Maker\r\nBy sponsoring this event, it puts you and your organization in an elite cadre of firms working to promote and improve STEM education.  The CCIC is a joint effort of the Governor’s Office of Business and Economic Development (Go-Biz) and Cal Poly San Luis Obispo’s California Cybersecurity Institute. To donate either financially or other forms of support, please contact Jimmy Baker at Jbaker30@calpoly.edu (703) 303-4233.\r\n \r\nTo learn more, visit http:&#047;&#047;cybercalifornia.biz  or contact Jimmy Baker at the CCI at jbaker30@calpoly.edu  or (703) 303-4233.\r\n \";s:10:\"department\";s:17:\"sales@8kmiles.com\";}', '2018-04-04 22:57:02'),
